The paper describes an approach to predicting dangerous seismic events in coal mines using machine learning. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of various predictive models, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) or information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of ensembles of models suggests a focus on data science (cs.DS).
